Chinese Vice-Premier Meets Croatian Cultural Minister
BEIJING , February 27 ( Xinhua ) -- Chinese Vice-Premier and Foreign Minister Qian Qichen met today with Croatian Cultural Minister Bozo Biskupic .
Qian expressed satisfaction with cooperation in various fields since the two nations forged diplomatic relations six years ago .
Qian said that joint efforts will ensure the long-term stable development of friendly bilateral ties and cooperation .
Biskupic noted that Croatia attaches great importance to China 's important position and role in the international arena and is eager to advance friendly ties .
He expressed appreciation for China 's consistent stand in support of Croatia 's independence , sovereignty and territorial integrity during the crisis in the former Yugoslavia .
Biskupic presented President Jiang Zemin with a letter from Croatian President Franjo Tudjman .
The Croatian delegation is visiting China at the invitation of the Ministry of Culture .
